<text top="764" left="1028" width="40" height="40" font="2">24</text>
<text top="57" left="401" width="369" height="60" font="3"><b>Chapter Goals</b></text>
<text top="179" left="65" width="398" height="47" font="4">• Distinguish among </text>
<text top="179" left="463" width="206" height="47" font="5">categories </text>
<text top="179" left="669" width="211" height="47" font="4">of numbers</text>
<text top="240" left="65" width="218" height="47" font="4">• Describe </text>
<text top="240" left="283" width="190" height="47" font="5">positional </text>
<text top="240" left="473" width="150" height="47" font="4">notation</text>
<text top="300" left="65" width="200" height="47" font="5">• Convert </text>
<text top="300" left="264" width="648" height="47" font="4">numbers in other bases to base 10</text>
<text top="361" left="65" width="200" height="47" font="5">• Convert </text>
<text top="361" left="264" width="714" height="47" font="4">base-10 numbers to numbers in other </text>
<text top="411" left="105" width="112" height="47" font="4">bases</text>
<text top="471" left="65" width="288" height="47" font="4">• Describe the </text>
<text top="471" left="353" width="227" height="47" font="5">relationship </text>
<text top="471" left="580" width="388" height="47" font="4">between bases 2, 8, </text>
<text top="522" left="105" width="129" height="47" font="4">and 16</text>
<text top="582" left="65" width="903" height="47" font="4">• Explain the importance to computing of bases </text>
<text top="633" left="105" width="154" height="47" font="4">that are </text>
<text top="633" left="260" width="217" height="47" font="5">powers of 2</text>
</page>
